<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[667,1194,964,1759]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3059913894" collectingDate="1902-02-14" collectingDateMax="1902-03-30" collectingDateMin="1902-02-14" collectionCode="AMNH" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" specimenCode="AMNH 666569, AMNH 666563, 666564" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Hartert designated as type of 
<emphasis box="[1040,1166,1174,1197]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">brevipennis</emphasis>
a male from Kiungchau collected on 
<date pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-02-14">
<collectingDate pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-02-14">14 February 1902</collectingDate>
</date>
. 
<specimenCode box="[819,1008,1233,1255]" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH 666569</specimenCode>
bears a Rothschild type label, indicating that it was Hartert’s chosen type, was cataloged in 
<collectionCode box="[667,760,1323,1344]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH</collectionCode>
as the type, and has always been considered as such. There are, however, three male specimens collected on that date. In order to validate Hartert’s chosen type and to remove the ambiguity, I hereby designate 
<specimenCode box="[667,853,1470,1492]" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH 666569</specimenCode>
the 
<typeStatus box="[910,1015,1470,1492]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[1060,1186,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">brevipennis</emphasis>
. Hartert had specimens from Kiungchau and Hoihow when he named 
<emphasis box="[965,1091,1529,1552]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">brevipennis</emphasis>
, but did not enumerate them. The following 
<typeStatus pageId="40" pageNumber="40">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
are in 
<collectionCode box="[864,961,1589,1610]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH</collectionCode>
: Hoihow, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">
<specimenCode collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH 666563</specimenCode>
, 
<specimenCode box="[771,853,1618,1639]" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">666564</specimenCode>
</emphasis>
, two males, 14, 
<date pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-03-30">
<collectingDate pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-03-30">30 March 1902</collectingDate>
</date>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3059913611" collectingDate="1902-02-13" collectingDateMax="1902-03-01" collectingDateMin="1902-02-13" collectionCode="AMNH" collectorName="Katsumata." pageId="40" pageNumber="40" specimenCode="AMNH 666565-666568, 6665670-666574" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
Kiungchau, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">
<specimenCode box="[900,1188,1648,1669]" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">AMNH 666565–666568</specimenCode>
, 
<specimenCode box="[667,857,1678,1699]" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">6665670–666574</specimenCode>
</emphasis>
, six males, three females, 
<date pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-02-13" valueMax="1902-03-01" valueMin="1902-02-13">
<collectingDate pageId="40" pageNumber="40" value="1902-02-13" valueMax="1902-03-01" valueMin="1902-02-13">13 February–1 March 1902</collectingDate>
</date>
(one dated 30 February!), all collected by 
<collectorName box="[994,1131,1738,1759]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Katsumata.</collectorName>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
